value.0: This is a fine set of metal bracers, the kind required for magical enhancement.
This is an iron breast plate. It should provide a suitable amount of protection from attacks.
This is an iron chain shirt. It should provide a suitable amount of protection from attacks.
These iron gauntlets appear to have seen some use, particularly in settling conflicts without resorting to the sword.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
This is a hammered iron helmet. It should provide a suitable amount of protection.
This is a hammered iron large shield. It should provide a suitable amount of protection.
This is a suit of iron scale mail. It should provide a suitable amount of protection from attacks.
This is a hammered iron small shield. It should provide a small amount of protection.
This well maintained helmet is commonly worn by crusaders and their ilk.
This well made battleaxe was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The battleaxe consist of a single blade atop a three or four foot shaft.  It is a versatile weapon, and remains a useful tool when not in combat.
This well made dagger was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
A basic but versatile weapon, the dagger consists of a double-edged piercing blade that typically ranges from about six to 24 inches in length.
This well made greataxe was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
A favorite of barbarians, the greataze is the larges of the weapons derived from the basic woodcutter's axe.  The double-edged head is far more suited to cleaving opponents than trees.
This well made halberd was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The halberd is the most common polearm, and could be called a cross between a spear and an axe.  Such weapons are often mass-produced for militia, and serve well when defending against marauders.
This well made heavy flail was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
Derived from a farm implement used for threshing grain, the heavy flail consists of a four-foot wooden shaft attached to a heavy or spiked head by a chain or hinge.
This well made mace was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The mace is a derivative of the basic club, consisting of a stone or metal head mounted on the end of a wooden shaft.  The weight of the head greatly increases the force of the impact.
This well made morningstar was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.

The morningstar is a derivative of the mace that includes a chain tether - similar to the flail - to add velocity when swinging its compact striking surface.  Morningstars commonly have at least one formidable spike as an added feature of the head.
This well made scimitar was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The scimitar shares some similarities with the longsword and other slashing blades, but the severity and thickness of its curve clearly sets it apart.
This well made spear was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
Another of history's most basic weapons, the spear is nevertheless a formidable weapon.  Little more than a simple shaft topped with a sharpened head, the spear is the staple of many a militia.
This well made warhammer was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
Originally adapted from the tools of laborers and craftsmen, the warhammer is a far-heavier variant of the sledge and is no longer suitable for anything but combat.
